"title": "5378: law, OT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5378: law, ot",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>OT laws and legal traditions govern every aspect of the life of the covenant people of God.</p>\n<h2>Kinds of OT law</h2>\n<h3>Criminal law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:12-Exod21:14\">EXO 21:12–21:14</a></strong> <em>Criminal law deals with crimes against persons punishable by a court.</em></p>\n<h3>Civil law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:18-Deut16:20\">DEU 16:18–16:20</a></strong> <em>Civil law deals with the upholding in court of legally established rights against possible abuse.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12-Deut15:18\">DEU 15:12–15:18</a></p>\n<h3>Social law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:21-Exod22:22\">EXO 22:21–22:22</a></strong> <em>Social law deals with behaviour or standards of behaviour which are not strictly enforceable in the courts.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:19-Deut24:22\">DEU 24:19–24:22</a></p>\n<h3>Cultic law</h3>\n<p>Cultic law deals explicitly with the ritual or religious life of the people of God. Leviticus chapters 1–7 are totally devoted to this kind of law:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:10-Lev1:13\">LEV 1:10–1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:13-Lev4:21\">LEV 4:13–4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:11-Lev7:18\">LEV 7:11–7:18</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of OT law</h2>\n<h3>Conditions for freeing servants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:2-Exod21:6\">EXO 21:2–21:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12-Deut15:18\">DEU 15:12–15:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:3-Exod21:11\">EXO 21:3–21:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:39-Lev25:55\">LEV 25:39–25:55</a></p>\n<h3>Dealing with injuries</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:23-Exod21:25\">EXO 21:23–21:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:38\">MAT 5:38</a></p>\n<h3>Property is to be protected</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:1\">EXO 22:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:1-Lev6:7\">LEV 6:1–6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8\">LUK 19:8</a></p>\n<h3>The rights of aliens must be respected</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:21\">EXO 22:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:33\">LEV 19:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:19\">DEU 10:19</a></p>\n<h3>Justice must be universally respected</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:2-Exod23:3\">EXO 23:2–23:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:15\">LEV 19:15</a></p>\n<h3>The Sabbath must be observed by all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:12\">EXO 23:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:8-Exod20:11\">EXO 20:8–20:11</a></p>\n<h3>Three annual festivals are to be celebrated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:15-Exod23:16\">EXO 23:15–23:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:17\">EXO 12:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:16\">DEU 16:16</a></p>\n<h3>Worship must be in accordance with God's will and must be kept pure</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:1-Deut12:7\">DEU 12:1–12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:6-Deut13:8\">DEU 13:6–13:8</a></p>\n<h3>Certain foods are declared to be unclean</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:1-Lev11:23\">LEV 11:1–11:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:3-Deut14:20\">DEU 14:3–14:20</a></p>\n<h3>A tenth of all produce must be given to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:22\">DEU 14:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:30\">LEV 27:30</a></p>\n<h3>Cultic laws are grounded in the holiness of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44\">LEV 11:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:1-Lev19:2\">LEV 19:1–19:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:16</a>LEV <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:3\">1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:1-Lev2:2\">LEV 2:1–2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:1-Lev3:2\">LEV 3:1–3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:27-Lev4:28\">LEV 4:27–4:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:17-Lev5:18\">LEV 5:17–5:18</a></p>\n<h3>Rules governing infectious or contagious diseases</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:2\">LEV 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:13\">LEV 15:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>There must not be unlawful sexual relations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:6\">LEV 18:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>A Day of Atonement must be held</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:26-Lev23:32\">LEV 23:26–23:32</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:2-Lev16:34\">LEV 16:2–16:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:7-Num29:11\">NUM 29:7–29:11</a></p>",
